  "text": "The HTTP filter chain extension mechanism in Envoy v1.31.2 is defined through a modular architecture spanning multiple key files:\n\n## Factory Registry and Extension Interfaces\n\nThe `envoy/server/filter_config.h` file defines the factory interfaces that plugins must implement. The `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` (lines 273-307) is the primary interface for HTTP filter factories, providing `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` method to create filter factory callbacks. Similarly, `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigFactory` (lines 309-324) serves upstream HTTP filters. These factories are registered in a global registry and discovered dynamically.\n\n## Filter Chain Factory and Manager Interfaces\n\nThe `envoy/http/filter_factory.h` file defines the core abstractions:\n- `FilterFactoryCb` (line 24): A function typedef that wraps filter creation - it receives `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` and installs filters\n- `FilterContext` (lines 30-37): Metadata about the filter including config_name and filter_name\n- `FilterChainOptions` (lines 45-58): Options for customizing filter chain creation, including filter disable logic\n- `FilterChainManager` (lines 70-81): Interface provided to factories to register filters via `applyFilterFactoryCb()`\n- `FilterChainFactory` (lines 89-119): Main factory interface that creates filter chains for new streams\n\n## Filter Interfaces\n\nThe `envoy/http/filter.h` file defines the filter plugin interfaces:\n- `StreamDecoderFilter` (lines 904-906): Interface for processing incoming requests\n- `StreamEncoderFilter` (lines 1120-1122): Interface for processing outgoing responses\n- `StreamFilter` (line 1190): Combined encoder/decoder filter\n- `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` (lines 1224-1257): Callbacks provided to factories to add filters to the chain (addStreamDecoderFilter, addStreamEncoderFilter, addStreamFilter, addAccessLogHandler)\n\n## Filter Chain Execution\n\nThe `source/common/http/filter_manager.h` file implements the actual filter chain execution:\n- `FilterManager` class (lines 638-1088): Manages the per-request filter chain, maintaining lists of decoder and encoder filters\n- `ActiveStreamFilterBase` (lines 65-101+): Base wrapper for active filters, handling state transitions and iteration control\n- `DownstreamFilterManager` (lines 1094-1200+): Specialized manager for downstream filters that handles local replies\n\nThe `source/common/http/filter_manager.cc` file contains the execution logic, with methods like `decodeHeaders()` (line 569) that iterates through decoder filters and handles their status returns.\n\n## Filter Chain Construction and Configuration\n\nThe `source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h` file provides utilities for building filter chains:\n- `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` (lines 55-57): Creates filters from a list of factory providers, handling disabled filters and missing configs\n- `FilterChainHelper` template (lines 68-201): Generic helper for processing filter configurations from protobuf, supporting both static and dynamic filter loading\n\nThe `source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.h` file implements the filter registry and dynamic configuration:\n- `NamedHttpFilterFactoryCb` struct (lines 185-190): Pairs a canonical filter name with its factory callback\n- `HttpFilterConfigProviderManagerImpl` (lines 651-661): Manages HTTP filter config providers\n- `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigProviderManagerImpl` (lines 678-687): Manages upstream filter providers\n- `HttpDynamicFilterConfigProviderImpl` (lines 195-233): Handles dynamic filter configuration via ECDS (Extension Config Discovery Service)\n\n## Request Processing Pipeline\n\nWhen an HTTP stream is created (from `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc` line 1132), the flow is:\n1. `ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStream::decodeHeaders()` is invoked with request headers\n2. It calls `FilterManager::decodeHeaders()` to start filter chain iteration\n3. The FilterManager iterates through decoder filters in order, calling their decode methods\n4. Each filter returns a status (Continue, StopIteration, etc.) that controls further iteration\n5. After request processing, response encoding follows the reverse path through encoder filters\n\nThe filter chain is built lazily per-request through the `FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()` interface (line 697 in filter_manager.h), which receives FilterContext and the factory callback, allowing dynamic filter instantiation based on runtime conditions.\n\nThis architecture enables:\n- **Extensibility**: New filters are added by implementing NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory and registering via the plugin system\n- **Per-request customization**: Filters can be enabled/disabled via route-level configuration or match trees\n- **Dynamic configuration**: Filters can be loaded dynamically via ECDS without Envoy restart\n- **Type-safe iteration**: The ActiveStreamFilterBase system ensures filters are called in correct order with proper state management\n"
